so manam rasina language ni system ardam chesukovali ante we need compiler/interpreter
why we need both..?
--. compiler anedhi rasina code ni motham vakesari machine understandable lang lo convert chesthadhi
-- interpreter anedhi line by line convert chesthadhi
speed anedhi compiler ne yekkuva
java anedhi both compiler & interpreter lang adhe python ayithe interpreter lang(python is slow)

why only java..?
java anedhi almost 27years nunchi vundhi (ante trustable)
-->large community across world wide (ante em ayina issue vachina ah issue someone might face and their will be solution for that)
--> libraries and framework(springboot)  (ante already half code build ayyi vuntadhi, no need to start from scratch)
-->** backward compatability (ante for ex py2 tisukunte dhantlo rasina code py3 lo work avvadhu adhe java lo ayithe java1 lo rasina code kuda 
    java20 lo work avvudhi)-- main imp

features--
java anedhi platform independent (ante nvu windows lo rasina code, mac Linux lo kuda work avvudhi)
-> but how?
vaka program rasaka adhi compile chesaka(javac helloworld.java) adhi .class file create chesthundhi
--> ee . class file not a highlevel/machine level language edhi intermediatecode/byte code, edhi ye platform midha ayina work avvudhi
2) objectoriented-- java lo anni classes and objects ne vuntay
3)memorymanagement-- manam yenno objects create chesthu vuntam code rasetappdu, unused vi anni clean cheyyali ante manaki kastam ,ikkada java anedhi
  garbagecollection dwara edhe memory clean chesthundhi
4) strongly typed -- ante nvu vaka dhanini define cheyyali anukunte adhi nvu mundhe declare cheyyali ex: int a=100; so compile time lo ne java ki telusthadhi
  edhi int type. adhe python lo ayithe a=100; anni rayochu edhi runtime lo ye type anedhi telusukuntadhi so python is slow
5) multithreaded : vake time lo diff methods ni execute cheyyagaladhu

