java lo yedhi ayina 1st we need to have class
class(template) ante like plan --> class create chesina antha matrana memory em create avvadhu
object like building --> java lo yedhi ayina manam objects tho ne chestham

public static void main(String[] args)

public ---> can access to anyone
execution anedhi main method nunchi start avvudhi
--manaki methods/variables anevi static/non-static(intsnace) vuntay
static anevi class load avvuthunnapude load avvuthay(jvm lo classloader), it doesn't require any object
so manam ikkada main method ni static ani declare chestham because if we dont declare main method as static
we need to create object to call the main method but execution anedhi main method nunche start avvvudhi appudu
object yela create avvvudhi so deadlock situation araise avvudhi
--instance method we need objects for this , vakavela object lekapothe instance methods ki asalu life ne vundadhu
--jvm anedhi 1st main method ni vethukoni akkada nunchi execution start avvudhi

** can we have overloaded methods for main method?
psvm(string[] args), psvm(int[] args) , yes we can have but jvm anedhi psvm(string[] args ne execute chesthadhi)
---psvm(int[] args) ee method execute cheyyali ante, in the psvm(string[] args){main();} manam call cheyyali
-- void main method ki return type em vundadhu
-- main it is the name of the main method


         Datatypes
Identifiers: it should be unique ,classes ki varaibles ki objects ki manam eche names
java lo primitive and non-primitive datatypes vunnay
primitive lo total 8 vunnay
numeric      char               Boolean
numeric lo malli 
byte - 1byte, short - 2bytes, int - 2bytes, float - 4bytes,long - 8bytes, doble - 8 bytes
char - 2 bytes, Boolean (true/false)- 1byte float f=0.2f; float ani compiler cheppadaniki f ani estham ledhante double type lo tisukuntadhi
char anedhi single character String anedhi grp of characters.
**String anedhi endhuku class not a datatype?
String lo manaki chala features lo vunnay so edhi class adhe byte int evi tisukunte vitiki em features em lev, its just datatype
java anedhi not a 100% object-oriented because ikkada primitive datatypes use chesthunam evi objects kadhu
-- prathi datatype ki wrapper class vunnay avi Byte,Short,Int,Float ila vitiki konni features vuntay.
--** same identifier tho diff datatypes ni evvocha ante like char c='a', int c=10; not we would get an error

