                        variables
 manaki local, static, non-static(instance) 3 types vuntay
 local variables anevi stack area lo store avvuthay
 yedhi ayina method/block lo create chesthe avi local variable ante m1 ane method create cheste nvu
 m1(){int a=100,int b=200;} evi local varibles. dhini scope ah method varake
 local varaibles ki manam ye access modifiers evvakudadhu except final
 outside the method u cant access those variables
 vitiki default vlues em vundavu
 lcal variable anevi method or code block excecute avvuthunappudu create avvuthay, method execution ayyipovagane destroy avvuthay
                  instance variables 
 instance variables anevi outside the method or constructor or any block
 vitini access cheyyali ante manam through object dwara ne cheyyagalam
 instance ante objects
 class Name{
   String name;
  psvm(String args[]){
  Name n=new Name();
  s.o.p(n.Name);}
 --ye access modifier ayina evvochu
 -- evi heap area lo store avvuthay
 --evi like global varaibles but only through object thone access cheyyagalam
 instance variables ki default values vuntay
--these variables can be set in multiple ways
  1) declare chesinappudu(int a=100;)
  2) through constructor
 3) through getters and setters
 4)through object reference(obj.a=100;)



imp***
static variable anevi method area lo store avvuthay
-- evi class load avvuthunnapude load avvuthay
-- ye access modifier ayina evvochu
--vitini manam class name tho access chestham
--static variables are not constant everyone telling like static variable are constants but its not true
--constants varible ki static estham manam
--ante for ex: company name tisukunte adhi employee andhariki same
-- so company name anedhi constant dhiniki manam static ane keyword assign chestham
-- static variables ki memory vakasare allocate avvudhi
--instance variables ki ayithe object create chesina prathi sari allocate avvuthadhi memory
   for ex:
  class Employee{
    int id;
    String name;
   Static String companyName=Mphasis;
   psvm(String[] args){
     Employee e=new Employee();
     e.id=5
     e.name="sree";
    s.o.p(e.id+" "+e.name+" "+e.companyName);--->5, sree, Mphasis
    Employee e1=new Employee();
    e1.id=1;
    e1.name="mouni";
    s.o.p(e1.id+" "+e1.name+" "+e1.companyName);--->1, mouni,Mphasis

    eppudu nenu e1.companyName="TCS" ani change chesthe , change avvutadhi
   s.o.p(e.companyNmae+" "+e1.companyName)---->tcs tcs ani print avvuthay
   ante static ani echina change avvuthay which means static variables are not constant
   but manam value change avvakunda vundali ante em cheyyali
   dhaniki static final companyNmae="Mphasis" appudu value change avvadhu
  -- ikkada whats the use of static i.e memory allocating only one time
***Test t=new Test();  --> ikkada new Test() anedhi heap lo store avvuthadhi, t anedhi ref variable edhi stack lo store avvuthadhi

                 Constructor
Constructor anedhi variables ni initialize cheyyadaniki use chestham
same as class name vundali, return type(int,void, string...) emi vundadhu
object create chesinappude default ga compiler anedhi vaka constructor ni create chesthadhi ,manam create cheyyakapoyina
